    <svcsubsec id="s15.4">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc id="s15.4.1" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Camshaft Bushings</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate new camshaft bushings and crankcase bores with clean engine oil.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450015024" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM07/M07109.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installation of cam bushing</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft bushing</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft bushing remover/installer (expanding collet) ZTSE4489</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Pulling screw (from camshaft bushing kit ZTSE2893A)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide a new bushing onto
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_325.xml" xrefid="s15.t3">camshaft bushing remover/installer (expanding
                        collet) ZTSE4489
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s15.t3"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Thread pulling screw (from camshaft bushing kit ZTSE2893A), backup nut, and
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_325.xml" xrefid="s15.t3">camshaft bushing remover/installer (expanding
                        collet) ZTSE4489
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s15.t3"/>
                    together.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten expanding collet by turning backup nut until bushing is securely held on
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_325.xml" xrefid="s15.t3">camshaft bushing remover/installer (expanding
                        collet) ZTSE4489
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s15.t3"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, ensure correct oil circulation through the crankcase. Align camshaft
                        bushing oil holes with corresponding oil supply holes machined in crankcase.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To aid in alignment of bushing and upper crankcase assembly oil holes, use a marker to
                    indicate oil hole location on backup nut of installation tool. Repeat this step for each camshaft
                    bushing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install all camshaft bushings through rear of upper crankcase assembly. Pull bushings in
                    place at rear of upper crankcase assembly by turning pulling nut on pulling screw until bushing is
                    flush on both sides with upper crankcase assembly. Remove
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_325.xml" xrefid="s15.t3">camshaft bushing remover/installer (expanding
                        collet) ZTSE4489
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s15.t3"/>
                    and inspect oil hole alignment.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
